Android Studio BlueFire API Build Instructions


**************************** Android Studio *******************************

1. Ensure the Simulate property is set to false in APITest/BlueFire.java.

2. Copy APITest/*.java to APILib/*.java (just changed files).

3. Clean/Build APILib. - IMPORTANT! Ensure Build Configuration dropdown is on APILib

4. If any changes were made to Main.java do the following;

    a. Edit APITest/Main.java and reverse commented package definition (top lines) and imports (bottom of imports), and save.

    b. Copy APITest/Main.java to BlueFire-API-for-Android/APIDemo/Main.java (if any changes were made).

    c. Edit APIDemo/Main.java and remove the commented package definition (top line), and save.

    d. Undo the changes made to APITest/Main.java and save.

5. Copy APILib aar path and sub-project name (below) for use in the next step.
    C:\Development\BlueFire\Android\API\APILib\build\outputs\aar\APILib-debug.aar bluefire-api-vxx.x

6. Import New Module APILib into BlueFire-API-for-Android (File/New/New Module/Import JAR/AAR Package).

7. Refactor blufire-api.vxx/APILib.debug.aar to bluefire-api-vxx.aar then press the Do Refactor button (under Project structure).

8. Open APIDemo Settings (right click/Open Module Settings).

9. Remove previous api dependency.

10. Remove previous api module.

11. Add new Module dependency bluefire-api-vxx.x.

12. Delete previous api folder.

13. Change VersionName in AndroidManifest.xml and build.gradle.

14. Clean/Build/Test APIDemo. Verify version and no Beta in title.

15. Copy External Libraries/bluefire-api-vxx.x/unspecified/classes.jar to libs folder.
    Note, the jar file can be verified by expanding classes.jar and examining the classes.
    Note, must copy the file from Windows Explorer (right click, Show in Explorer).

16. Rename libs/classes.jar to bluefire-api.vxx.x.jar.

17. Build APK from Build tab.

18. Make changes to README.md.

19. Commit/Push to GitHub - Set Commit Message to Update to Version xx.x.

**************************** Eclipse *******************************

1. Open Eclipse.

2. Copy Studio/Main.java to Eclipse/Main.java (and layout/Main.xml if form changed).

3. Copy Studio/AndroidManifest.xml to Eclipse/AndroidManifest.xml.

4. Copy Studio/libs/bluefire-api-vxx.x.jar to Eclipse/libs.

5. Delete previous Eclipse/Libs/bluefire-api-vxx.x.jar.

6. Edit and copy changed contents of Studio/README.md to Eclipse/README.md.

7. Clean, Build, and Test APIDemo. NOTE - Must Test to build APK.

8. Ensure APIDemo.apk is in the bin folder.

9. Commit/Push to GitHub. Set Commit Message to Update to Version xx.x.
